      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear u, but when u say \"rules-based order,\" doesn't that sound a bit like the US is just defining the rules to benefit themselves? like, if china thinks they have historical rights to those waters, isn't the US basically just calling their claims \"illegal\" or \"wrong\" because they don't fit the Western model? feels like the \"order\" is just a way to delegitimize anything that isn't US-led.",
